-- Air France to Look at Job Cuts on June 21, Les Echos Reports
-- B y   C a r o l   M a t l a c k
-- 2012-06-13T05:49:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/air-france-to-look-at-job-cuts-on-june-21-les-echos-reports.html
Air France (AF)  will identify possible
job cuts at a meeting of the airline’s central committee on June
21,  Les Echos  reported, citing labor union sources.  The reductions, part of a plan to cut costs by 2 billion
euros ($2.5 billion) by 2015, would involve only ground
personnel, who account for 32,000 of Air France’s 53,000
employees, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carol Matlack in Paris at 
 cmatlack@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
